In this press briefing, President Trump discusses various topics, including border security, the wall, and immigration. He emphasizes the need for extreme border security and surveillance, as well as the importance of the wall. He clarifies that they are not considering citizenship or amnesty for DREAMers, but rather allowing them to stay in the country. He also addresses the issue of a potential deal with Democrats and the importance of the wall in any agreement. On the topic of tax reform, President Trump focuses on benefiting the middle class and creating jobs. He mentions the goal of reducing the tax rate to around 15 percent and bringing companies and money back to the US. He stresses that his priority is jobs and the middle class.